173
00:09:56,120 --> 00:10:00,600
 A state machine is a thing that works in steps.

174
00:10:02,460 --> 00:10:06,840
 On every step, the state machine gets a new input.

175
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:11,539
 Then based on that input and its memory of what's come

176
00:10:11,539 --> 00:10:14,659
 before, the state machine decides to do something.

177
00:10:14,799 --> 00:10:15,679
 It generates an output.

178
00:10:16,019 --> 00:10:17,240
 And then the process repeats.

179
00:10:19,919 --> 00:10:23,460
 We will see that that kind of an abstraction, state

180
00:10:23,460 --> 00:10:26,720
 state machines, there's a way to think about state machines

181
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:31,980
 that is compositional, that you can think of as a hierarchy

